I am a descendant of Korean who got hurt by Japanese imperialism and militarism. I am seeking an urgent apology for the thumbnail of the CWC video; rising-sun flag backgrounded one. It is becoming a concern, a huge concern all over Korea. Some might say, "it is just a thumbnail," but it isn't. The rising-sun symbol is literally a nazi symbol or Hakenkreuz to all Asians. Japanese militarism colonized, killed, and enslaved Asians with the symbol which represents Japanese. The action Japanese militarism did to Asians contains forced labor; removing Korean/Chinese/other cultures from the people they colonized; forced comfort women at war sides; torturing/having experiences with live human bodies; and even more. The flag and the symbol which has been uploaded is being offendedly accepted to Korean. I and Koreans need a sincere apology from LFC. Moreover, I hope this event to turn to an opportunity for LFC to remind german nazism to the rising-sun flag. The meaning of the symbol and what Japanese militarism have done to uncountable numbers of Asians are hoping to be concerned, too. The rising-sun symbol is not a 'cool' symbol. It is a horrifying and terrifying symbol that makes numbers of people to feel being offended and hurt. The mistake shall not be taken again, LFC.


(Wondering why is the apology only available in Korea, written in 'non-apology apology' sense. We are looking for a sincere and quick apology which is posted online globally.)
